-- Continental, UAL agree on exchange ratio: source
-- 
-- Fri Apr 30, 2010 12:07pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/04/30/us-airlines-united-idUSTRE63S67E20100430

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Continental Airlines Inc CAL.N and UAL Corp's UAUA.O United Airlines have agreed to an exchange ratio of 1.05 UAL shares for each Continental share in a deal that would create the world's largest carrier, a source briefed on the matter said. 

 United's board will meet Friday, while Continental's board will hold meetings on Friday and Sunday to discuss the deal, the source said. An announcement could come as early as Sunday, the source said. (Reporting by  Jui Chakravorty , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)